     we have</para><equation id="eip-112"><m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>v</m:mi>
<m:mrow><m:mtext>w</m:mtext><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:mrow>
</m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mtext>38</m:mtext><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>0 m/s</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mtext>–0</m:mtext><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>342</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mtext>=–13</m:mtext><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>0 m/s.</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{v rSub { size 8{wx} } = \( "38" "." "0 m/s" \)  \( "–0" "." "342" \) "=–13" "." "0 m/s."} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math></equation><para id="import-auto-id1458785">The minus sign indicates motion west which is consistent with the diagram.</para>
    <para id="import-auto-id1608146">Now, to find <m:math>
